Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Festivals have been the source of measles cases this summer [2016] in the UK. Since more festivals will be taking place, such as the Reading Festival, there are concerns that this could lead to further outbreaks. Measles is a highly infectious viral illness that can be very unpleasant and sometimes lead to serious complications; people -- especially those attending festivals in the UK or large gatherings anywhere where measles has been active this year -- should check their vaccination status.

The HealthMap/ProMED map of Wales and the UK may be accessed at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4416336,40 and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4416336,281 - Mod.LK]

